title: Convos With Cathy - Doubts, Grief, & Falling Off Stage
description:
Award winning rapper, Guvna B (aka Isaac Borquaye), chats to me about his journey into the music industry, some of his memorable stage snafus, how the sudden death of his dad affected him, and some of the ways that people in his life gave him the confidence to be vulnerable enough to find healing.

title: Artist Collective - Ad-Apt – You Got This
description:
The Artist Collective is a community of creatives from the performing arts, entertainment and music industry. Art shapes culture, and the goal of the Artist Collective is to create a space for present or future culture shapers to gather, to share their art & to get to know one another.

Historically we've gathered around London in person for intimate nights of live music, conversation and free pizza, and in this season we're switching online to keep those conversations going. Introducing the Artist Collective Podcast, hosted by the AC team, we'll be inviting all kinds of storytellers; from artists to producers, from directors to dancers, to have a chat, let us into their worlds & give up a behind the scenes look of the realities of creating art in the current climate.

The first episode is with artist/MC Ad-Apt, who is the front man for Wilkinson Live & co-founder of HYR London, who shares his wrestles with Lockdowns, feeling like and old and his hope for the future.
tag_list: hillsong church London faith jesus "artist collective"

title: Convos With Cathy - Cultivating Wild Dreams - Not Stereotypes
description:
I sat down for a chat with Shalyce Lawrence, founder of the Care Leaver’s Christmas Day that we now host at the Bermondsey Warehouse. We talk about what it was like going into foster care as a 6 year old who didn’t understand why, the misconception that sets back many kids in care, and what made her go on to start these Christmas dinners.

If you’d like to donate towards making this year’s Care Leaver’s Christmas Day possible, head to hillsong.co.uk/Christmas or via the Christmas Together section of our Hillsong App.

On the website or app:

Scroll down to Christmas Giving > click GIVE > choose your location > click the Christmas Giving dropdown menu > select Christmas Giving again to see more options > choose Care Leavers Christmas Day and input any amount

Dr. Laura Beveridge and Hans Buter of our Greenlight team talk to us about what our church is doing to change the narrative for rough sleepers in London, how personal connections with people in these situations has changed their view of homelessness, and the way that serving others has blessed them personally and deepened their relationship with God.

title: Convos With Cathy - Look Out - It’s White People!

title: Convos With Cathy - Do I Have To Go Church?
description:
As we look forward to this year’s A21 Walk for Freedom, the lovely Charlie Blythe talks to me about why fighting slavery is more necessary today than at any point in history, what she did when her mum gave her the option to quit church, her teenage battles with anxiety, and the realization that motherhood would not diminish her capacity but increase it.

Check out A21.org to find out more about how you can help A21 fight modern slavery, in both our local communities and around the globe.

title: Convos With Cathy - So I Stole That Bible…
description:
I had way too much fun hanging out with Mikey Carter and hearing all about how he went from selling drugs to touring the world as a dancer, and then having a supernatural encounter with God in a Munich hotel.  We also chat about how God has cultivated a heart in him to make people his passion and the transition he’s made from a career in performing arts to now serving at A21 UK, an anti-trafficking organisation.



And don’t forget to make plans to join us at this year’s A21 Walk for Freedom!  For more info and to register, check out a21.org/walk – see you there!

ZACKEY FORCE FUNK "Don't Fake The Funk" : Autobiography Intro
description:
Introduction chapter to ZACKEY FORCE FUNK's autobiography "DON'T FAKE THE FUNK" narrated by Zach Hose.  Available now on Audible:   www.audible.com/pd/Dont-Fake-the-Funk-Audiobook/B09J1NFNKL

"Do you know any four-time felons who’ve built groundbreaking rockets for SpaceX? You do now. His name is Zack Hose. During the day, the former career criminal is a respected structural specialist in aeronautics. Off the clock, unbeknownst to most coworkers, Hose is a modern funk music icon: Zackey Force Funk. The narrator of cholo-approved lowrider anthems, his helium-pitched croons and sensual whispers chronicle drug-fueled parties, romance, and recklessness. Gleaming synths and body rocking bass score every gritty detail. Don’t Fake the Funk is an autobiography that moves at the same breakneck speed Zackey has lived his entire life. It begins under Arizona’s scorching sun, where he went from a thriving teenage drug dealer to surviving the most dangerous prisons, and ends by the breeze-kissed coastline of Long Beach, CA. The often illicit three and a half decades he covers are stranger and more terrifying than anything he has committed to wax, but they are also poignant, hilarious, and inspirational. Somewhere between moving weight and becoming a father, Zackey had the spiritual awakening that led to both of his careers. Don’t Fake the Funk is a document of his radical transformation, a story of perseverance and positive thinking that will inspire anyone hoping to realize the impossible. "  

Blurb by Max Bell

title: 1. Align
description:
GRACE OH is a Visual and Sensory Healing Artist working with the mediums of Sound and Light.  She practices Sound Healing Therapy, Yoga, Reiki, Nutritional & Vibrational Cheffing as well as Photography & Videography.  Grace has a combination of a twenty-year journey in all the modalities and mediums she practices.  Inspired by travel and deep inner journeys that can happen in retreat settings, Grace began co-facilitating retreats in Bali, Yosemite & Tanzania in 2018.

'MOYO' is Grace Oh's first Sound Healing Album.  The album emphasizes a Sound Bath experience which is supported by the playing of Crystal Bowls, Vocal Toning, Tuning Forks, & Wind Chimes.  The pieces in the album are of recordings created from the timeline of 2017 - 2019 in Venice & Topanga, CA to the Serengeti of Tanzania.

HIT+RUN is honored to release 'MOYO' [HNR98] a crucial empathetic offering to planet Earth on Monday, November 30th (Beaver Full Moon) in both digital & vinyl record formats.  The 12" vinyl is a truly exquisite object to hold & gaze upon - a dense case-wrapped outer jacket deftly hand-screenprinted across the cover in crushed luminescent crystal beads, with a mesmerizing milky clear sound platter housed inside.  Limited to a strict 250 copies, these covetable vinyl pieces are available individually, or specially-bundled along with the vesica piscis-cover art silkscreened jute burlap bag & shimmering soft enamel pin (limited to just 33qty).  The 43-minute three-song album available on Bandcamp contains an additional three digital bonus tracks not on the physical format (and comes with all purchases).  Meticulously mastered separately for vinyl & digital formats by Jeremy Balliger in Venice, CA, with a consummate visual design by Brandy Flower.

Grace Oh is currently living and practicing in Venice, CA. You can find more information on Grace's work at www.loveartlifesounds.com as well as on Instagram @graceunheaoh.

title: N8NOFACE "IDGAF" (PREVIOUSLY UNRELEASED)
description:
Special double A-side 'DAY OF THE DEAD' single from N8NOFACE coming on 11/2/17. 

N8 was one half of underground synthpunk legends CRIMEKILLZ. Fresh off the Spring release of his stunning fourteen-song debut album "Stories Of Those' [HNR69], plus "Demos And Demons" [HNR81] the ten track collection of demos recorded between 2015-2016, this is the third release from producer / singer N8NOFACE in 2017, as well as a preview of his forthcoming 2018 album "True Story" [HNR90] due out next Spring.

Twenty-two highly limited-edition one-sided 7" collectible lathe cuts for the new N8NOFACE double A-side single "Say Goodbye / IDGAF". These previously unreleased tracks were cut in MONO on a round, clear polycarbonate disc in real time on a PRESTO 6N vintage lathe in Tucson, while the opposite side was screenprinted in black ink by HIT+RUN in downtown Los Angeles. Each lathe comes housed in a stamped white paper sleeve, inside a screenprinted monochrome glossy white outer jacket. Item arrives in a protective plastic sleeve, plus all orders receive a N8NOFACE "Demos And Demons" [HNR81] compact disc (featuring ten demos recorded from 2015-2016). Strict Edition of 22qty.

Produced by N8NOFACE 
Written by N. Hose 
Published by Nathan William Hose (ASCAP) 
Mastered by A.P. / GS Mastering & Post 
Design by Brandy Flower

title: Change
description:
As a multi-instrumentalist, producer, emcee & music educator, THAVIUS BECK is a man whose life revolves around audio and technology. With a focus on bass heavy rhythms, dark, emotional melodies and twisted sample manipulation, Thavius has not only released numerous solo albums (under his own name, plus previous moniker Adlib), but he's also collaborated with and remixed luminaries Saul Williams, Nine Inch Nails, The Mars Volta, Skylar Grey and Nas, to name a few.

A native of Minneapolis, THAVIUS BECK moved to Los Angeles at age 16 and quickly found a crew of like-minded beat makers & rappers who formed the underground hip-hop collective known as Global Phlowtations. As a main pillar of the nine-man (and one woman) crew, he was responsible for producing, rhyming on and recording many of the songs that were released across three classic self-released GPAC albums in the late 90's. Thavius released solo projects through various labels over his 20-year stay in LA, collaborated with fellow producer/emcee Subtitle (aka Giovanni Marks) to create the group "Labwaste", and began touring with Saul Williams as his 'one-man band', armed with assorted electronic gadgetry.

Eventually his love of music & technology lead to Ableton Live, for which he became a certified trainer of in 2009. Thavius quickly became a world-renowned advocate for Ableton Live education, and took a brief hiatus from releasing albums to run electronic music workshops and explore teaching. In 2016, he left the cozy confines of Los Angeles and relocated to Brooklyn, NY. Reinvigorated by the city, plus frequent European tours with Saul Williams, both inspired many meditative hours spent in hotels, planes & trains writing new material. 

The result is an impassioned new self-produced project "TECHNOL O.G." [HNR74], that finds Thavius expressing his true self as an artist & man. His much-anticipated twelve song album is a record full of raw & unfiltered truth revealed through his rhythmic vocal reflections and electronic production perfection. Released worldwide on Monday September 18th, 2017 on one-of-a-kind kaleidoscopic 12" colored vinyl, housed in a variety of hand-screenprinted and collectible outer jackets. 

Bandcamp downloads also include the stunning Mono/Poly remix of lead track "Spectacular Vernacular".

All Songs Written, Produced, Recorded & Mixed by Thavius Beck.
Published by 1000:1 (ASCAP) 
except: "Vices" (written by T. Beck & M. Parvizi)
Electric Guitar on "Vice": Mike Parvizi
Mastered by Jeremy Balliger @biffchitlins
Artwork by Jon Ramone @jon_ramone
Design by Brandy Flower

title: A Day in The Life...
description:
As a multi-instrumentalist, producer, emcee & music educator, THAVIUS BECK is a man whose life revolves around audio and technology. With a focus on bass heavy rhythms, dark, emotional melodies and twisted sample manipulation, Thavius has not only released numerous solo albums (under his own name, plus previous moniker Adlib), but he's also collaborated with and remixed luminaries Saul Williams, Nine Inch Nails, The Mars Volta, Skylar Grey and Nas, to name a few.

A native of Minneapolis, THAVIUS BECK moved to Los Angeles at age 16 and quickly found a crew of like-minded beat makers & rappers who formed the underground hip-hop collective known as Global Phlowtations. As a main pillar of the nine-man (and one woman) crew, he was responsible for producing, rhyming on and recording many of the songs that were released across three classic self-released GPAC albums in the late 90's. Thavius released solo projects through various labels over his 20-year stay in LA, collaborated with fellow producer/emcee Subtitle (aka Giovanni Marks) to create the group "Labwaste", and began touring with Saul Williams as his 'one-man band', armed with assorted electronic gadgetry.

Eventually his love of music & technology lead to Ableton Live, for which he became a certified trainer of in 2009. Thavius quickly became a world-renowned advocate for Ableton Live education, and took a brief hiatus from releasing albums to run electronic music workshops and explore teaching. In 2016, he left the cozy confines of Los Angeles and relocated to Brooklyn, NY. Reinvigorated by the city, plus frequent European tours with Saul Williams, both inspired many meditative hours spent in hotels, planes & trains writing new material. 

The result is an impassioned new self-produced project "TECHNOL O.G." [HNR74], that finds Thavius expressing his true self as an artist & man. His much-anticipated twelve song album is a record full of raw & unfiltered truth revealed through his rhythmic vocal reflections and electronic production perfection. Released worldwide on Monday September 18th, 2017 on one-of-a-kind kaleidoscopic 12" colored vinyl, housed in a variety of hand-screenprinted and collectible outer jackets. 

Bandcamp downloads also include the stunning Mono/Poly remix of lead track "Spectacular Vernacular".

title: Gangsigns
description:
Zackey Force Funk deserves (and receives) a lot of respect. If he's not robbing banks with baseball bats, roaming the streets for fat cats to hustle, or launching rockets into Space, you can usually find him leaning over the turntables of a dirty dirty late-night discotheque. Take off your kevlar, put down those batons – Zackey Force Funk comes in PEACE! This time… 

This quintessential eighteen track album compiles Zackey's first-ever recorded songs, demos & rarities originally incorporated into DJ Kutmah's "This Is The Force Funk Sound" [HNR03] megamix created for H+R way way back in Summer of 2009. Each classic song has been meticulously remastered for the very special release of "THIS IS MY FORCE FUNK SOUND" [HNR73]. Available on eye-boggling 12" Picture Disc vinyl, housed inside a shrink-wrapped full color cardboard jacket (*not screenprinted), as well as collectible Cassette Tapes, which both include the Bonus Tracks "Dirty Alley" & "John Carpenter". First Edition Pressing of 500qty 

Don't miss out on rare Test Pressings, Bundle packages with enamel Pins, Mini-bat Keychains, embroidered Hats, and please... DON'T FAKE THE FUNK.
publisher_metadata-album_title: This Is My Force Funk Sound  [HNR73] MP3

title: Punks
description:
Zackey Force Funk deserves (and receives) a lot of respect. If he's not robbing banks with baseball bats, roaming the streets for fat cats to hustle, or launching rockets into Space, you can usually find him leaning over the turntables of a dirty dirty late-night discotheque. Take off your kevlar, put down those batons – Zackey Force Funk comes in PEACE! This time… 

This quintessential eighteen track album compiles Zackey's first-ever recorded songs, demos & rarities originally incorporated into DJ Kutmah's "This Is The Force Funk Sound" [HNR03] megamix created for H+R way way back in Summer of 2009. Each classic song has been meticulously remastered for the very special release of "THIS IS MY FORCE FUNK SOUND" [HNR73]. Available on eye-boggling 12" Picture Disc vinyl, housed inside a shrink-wrapped full color cardboard jacket (*not screenprinted), as well as collectible Cassette Tapes, which both include the Bonus Tracks "Dirty Alley" & "John Carpenter". First Edition Pressing of 500qty 

Don't miss out on rare Test Pressings, Bundle packages with enamel Pins, Mini-bat Keychains, embroidered Hats, and please... DON'T FAKE THE FUNK.

Because they held it held the crown
How they held it held it down

title: HEADLOCK "Mad Diamonds" (Elusive Rmx) FREE DOWNLOAD
description:
ELUSIVE REMIXES HEADLOCK (FREE DOWNLOAD)

HEADLOCK "Gang Nativity" [HNR76] 
>> 08.08.17

@shredrap

+

Born from swampy house party revolutions in Portland and meeting somewhere at the intersection of concept art & hip-hop, rap duo HEADLOCK are a well-loved slice of the Tucson music community. TRICERATOP plays the beats, ILLSLUR puts down the raps, and together they've created "shredrap" a sound from dollar bin records, abandoned effects pedals, thrifted drum machines, heavy psych borrows and a VCR. While the fuzzy, almost abrasive production screams intensity, HEADLOCK draw from wide inspiration and land somewhere near the intersection of ILL MILITARY x EX COMMUNICATION. 

HEADLOCK's new self-produced six-song EP "Gang Nativity" [HNR76] is released worldwide on August 8th, 2017 via HIT+RUN. Available on limited-edition first pressing of AQUAMARINE colored 10" vinyl (each comes with an iron-on nun patch), hi-bias compact cassette tape (includes a 1" round nun button), plus the digital download features the exclusive bonus track "BARK ROAR" not available elsewhere.


PRODUCED BY HEADLOCK 
DUDES • ILLSLUR x TRICERATOP 
RECORDED + MIXED • THE LASSO 
MASTERED • SWARVYY 
NUN • YU YU SHIRATORI 
GANG • BOBBY CARLSON 
CREW • HIT+RUN 

ALL SONGS WRITTEN BY T. JOHNSON + N. KELSO 
PUBLISHED BY FUN PROFESSIONAL (ASCAP) / CHURCH OF HYPE (ASCAP)

title: zeroh "Snakes"
COTOWN "Bring Your Best Friend"
description:
FREE DOWNLOAD

"Bring Your Best Friend" is the fourth musical offering from HIT+RUN CREW in 2017. The track (Produced by Eludem)is a dense late-night escapade taken from the 10-track compilation "COTOWN: VOLUME ONE" [HNR72] out now on H+R.

"COTOWN" is the name Emmanuel Coto christened his Rampart home studio in Summer 2015, giving birth to the "COTOWN Sound". Numerous collaborators & talented friends passed through the threshold of COTOWN to jam, contribute, teach and learn. This highly industrious free-form environment quickly became a secret hub for LA creatives and left-field musicians.

2017 sees the official launch of the COTOWN Records label with this refreshingly diverse 10-song compilation available for download on Bandcamp for a special low price.

Recorded at COTOWN
Produced by Eludem 
Vocals by Coto
Mastered by A.P. / GS Mastering & Post
Art by Brandy Flower

title: KUTMAH "III Eye"
description:
Originally born in Brighton, England, Kutmah made his name while living & DJing in Los Angeles, releasing acclaimed mixes and building up connections with the Brainfeeder & Low End Theory crews. In 2010 he was deported to the UK, lived in London for 5 years and now resides in Berlin (while still holding down a show on the East London-based radio station NTS).

In Summer 2015, prolific left-field beat maker Kutmah released the 20-track instrumental beat album BLK/SMR via Bandcamp. During Summer 2016 he selected & sequenced his favorite ten tracks for a limited-edition 10" vinyl & cassette tape version of BLK/SMR [HNR67] on HIT+RUN.

"III Eye" is the third offering from this 24-minute EP.

title: Kingdom Building Conversations - Lamar Riddick
description:
Lamar Riddick is a Christian hip-hop artist who prides himself on his articulate and clear sound, passion for music, and his desire to empower.

His new project, “Nothing to Prove,” recently dropped and he took the time to share his heart behind the project, his journey, and future plans.

ABOUT THE ARTIST
Lamar Riddick is an award-winning Christian Hip Hop Artist in Morgantown, WV by way of Fort Lauderdale, FL. Lamar believes in Reviving the Culture through the use of his music and clothing brand in an effort to draw listeners closer to Jesus. 

Riddick’s style is energetic, bold, fierce, and some would even say gritty. He is currently the Program Assistant for the West Virginia University Marching Band, Owner of Revive Collective Music and Revive Collective Apparel, offers internships and jobs to local college students, serves in his community as an event coordinator, curator, and plays drums on the worship team at Mountain Heights Morgantown on Sunday Mornings.

Website: https://www.lamarriddickmusic.com/

title: Sup The Chemist - Kingdom Building Conversations
description:
It is impossible to consider Christian Hip Hop history without Chris Cooper a.k.a. Sup, a.k.a. Super C, a.k.a. Soup The Chemist. His "group" was S.F.C., which stood for Soldiers For Christ. SFC’s debut, Listen Up, brought food for a hungry market bringing authentic street rap with the best use of scratching and sampling heard to date. In-your-face lyrics dealt with real issues like drugs, gang violence, immoral living, and more. CCM Magazine called Listen Up a “welcome face in the growing genre of Christian rap.”

Soup wrote a book releasing in June titled, “Through My Windows”. It details the gospel rap movement from 1985 to 2003. For anyone seeking to understand how the movement started and how groups such as SFC, The Gospel Gangstas, I.D.O.L. King, Freedom of Soul, and Dynamic Twins came to be, this book is a must-read!

Personally (Trig speaking), Soup made a tremendous impact on how I viewed ministering live about twenty years ago, which I had never shared with him until this interview!

title: Gospel Gangstaz - Kingdom Building Conversations
description:
During my early Christian years, I (trig) was blessed to bump into The Cross Movement by way of my brother-in-law, O-Diggity, subsequently enjoying watching them finish Heaven’s Mentality and then getting engrossed in the Philadelphia and East-Coast CHH scene which included the early days of folks such as D.A. title: Dynamic Twins Kingdom Building Conversations Artist Interview
description:
On Juneteeth weekend, Darius West shared the @micdropthemovie premiere in #dallas, igniting an overdue celebration of many CHH Pioneers. It was an incredible weekend allowing artists to reconnect, fans to gain a deeper appreciation of the genre, and for all to take in their stories through the documentary.

During this interview, the Dynamic Twins share their background, pursuing their calling amid naysayers and standing firm in their beliefs. Did you they had an opportunity to blow up in Hollywood but said “no” to famous producer Mel Brooks when he asked them to compromise their values?

About the Dynamic Twins
The Dynamic Twins are a Bronx-born Christian rap group composed of identical twins Noel and Robbie Arthurton. The twins moved to California in 1989. They began to make guest appearances on albums by other Christian rap artists, including J.C. and the Boyz' and S.F.C.

The group's first album Word 2 the Wize released in 1991 through Broken/Brainstorm Artists International and was distributed to mainstream record stores through Epic Records. S.F.C.'s Chris Cooper helped with production chores and fellow S.F.C.'er The Dove added scratching. Also guesting was Crystal Lewis, whose album Simply the Best had included a song penned by Noel Arthurton.

The Twins' second album, No Room 2 Breathe, garnered praise from True Tunes magazine as a "landmark in the Christian rap industry" for basing itself musically around live instruments instead of programmed samples and beats.

The third album on B.A.I. was 40 Days in the Wilderness. As with all Dynamic Twins releases, it features many guest appearances, including Ayeesha, who was introduced into the scene on this album. Grapetree Records signed Ayeesha as their first female rapper.

The group received 3 Dove Awards nominations for their music and has appeared with well-known artists such as: Westside Connection, Fred Hammond, BeBe, and CeCe Winans, and Audio Adrenaline.

title: CStraight- Kingdom Building Conversations
description:
Welcome to another Kingdom Building Conversation, where we put Christ on display through those serving him in the culture.

During this interview, we discuss CStraight’s 10-year hiatus, the process of returning, God Chaserz’s 15-year anniversary, and more.

The newest release from GodChaserz Entertainment will be Cstraight’s sophomore album entitled “The View From Here.” After a 10-year hiatus, Cstraight is returning to give supporters a new addition to their GodChaszerz library. Cstraight is one of the pillars of GCE’s artist roster and has been featured on numerous projects through the years.

“This album is focused on looking at things the way that the Word of God sees them,” says Cstraight. Fans can expect the gritty and imaginative wordplay Cstraight is known for as well as some head nod vibes to ride to.

ABOUT THE ARTIST
Biography

Cstraight is a Christian Rap artist from Jacksonville, FL. Cstraight surrendered his life to Christ and immediately began his music career in his late teens under the name Likewise. His music is heavily influenced by his belief and faith in Jesus Christ as well as his life experiences. Cstraight has released 2 albums, 2 group albums & has been featured on many nationally released projects.

title: Angie Rose - Kingdom Building Conversations
description:
Welcome to another Kingdom Building Conversation, where we put Christ on display through those serving him in the culture.
During our discussion Angie unpacks the reality of being on a major record label, the journey getting there and the work to keep things aligned.  She shares why she started her series The Rose Confesses, which you can find on her Facebook channel (https://www.facebook.com/angierosemusik/), fighting with depression and the meaning behind her latest song 7 Gold Chains.

About The Artist
With nearly 5MM Global Career streams of her music and 2.5MM Channel views, Angie Rose does not need much introduction, she is a dynamic powerhouse Pop/Hip-Hop artist from the Bronx. 

From Puerto Rican roots, she inspires her fans to be unstoppable through a combination of raw energy and undaunted lyrics.  That’s an unbiased opinion as acknowledged by her features in People Magazine’s (En Espanol) HOT LIST, NYLON’s Soundcheck, Upscale Magazine and Hola Magazine.

Her music promotes diversity and overcoming all obstacles, pulling from her past experiences with loss, drugs, and hurt, which is probably when her song “Fight Like a Man,” was included on VH1’s Love & Hip-Hop last year.

title: Kingdom Building Conversations - Hulvey
description:
Hulvey went from being an avid Reach Records listener to a Reach Records artist. His new release, Christopher, is a diverse collection of artistic expressions that resonate with his comment during our interview of him wanting to give Reach fans even more. During our discussion, he shares life-changing moments, milestones of his journey, and more.

Bio:
Hulvey was discovered out of his hometown of Brunswick, GA- he has a fascinating story of going from dropping out of college, scrubbing toilets at Publix, to becoming Reach Records' latest breakout hip hop artist. His label debut project BRKNHRT released in 2020 and immediately garnered him national praise.  

Pandora named him “Christian Artist to Watch in 2020”, his tracks ‘Higher’ and ‘Real Love’ from Hulvey Vol. 1 and Hulvey Vol. 2 were featured on VH1’s Love and Hip Hop Atlanta in 2020 and ‘Cold Blooded’ was featured on ABC’s hit show ‘The Rookie’. Shortly after BRKNHRT released, the world shut down, entering into a global pandemic.  Having to put the hopes of touring and performing on hold, Hulvey, like the rest of the world, found himself in his bedroom, secluded from his friends and family, where he was forced to face his insecurities and fears and surrender them to God. It was then, his forthcoming album was born.

Project Pericles Forum: Iowa Caucuses (Febuary 6, 2020)
description: The first voting of the 2020 primary season has been completed with the conclusion of the Iowa Caucuses. Delphia Shanks, Assistant Professor of Politics will discuss the results and what it means for the candidates moving forward.  Contact Matt Moran at moran@hendrix.edu for more information.

title: Project Pericles Forum: The Cancel Culture (Nov 21, 2019)
description: This week's Project Pericles Forum examines the so-called "cancel culture." Jay Barth will facilitate the Forum: "The Cancel Culture: A Step Forward or a Hindrance to Equity?"

title: Project Pericles Forum: Diversity at Hendrix (Nov 7, 2019)
description: Kesha Baoua and Walter Pryor ’87, chair of the Board of Trustees’ Diversity and Inclusion committee, for this week’s Project Pericles Forum: “How Well is Diversity Working at Hendrix?”

title: First Tuesday Talk: Felipe Pruneda Senties  on Sharing the Process of his Identity (Nov 5, 2019)
description: The Office for Diversity and Inclusion and Project Pericles presents Dr. Pruneda speakiong on why he believes it is so important to destabilize our certainties about who we are from time to time.

title: Project Pericles Forum: Epidemics Past, Present, and Future (Oct 31, 2019)
description: This week's Project Pericles Forum, co-facilitated by Dr. Sasha Pfau and Dr. Laura MacDonald will grapple with public responses to epidemics: “Science/Community: What Is the Value of Government During Epidemics?”

title: Project Pericles Forum: Towards Climate Resilience(Oct 10, 2019)
description: In the wake of the Global Climate Strike, Tristan Norman ’20 and Dr. William Haden Chomphosy will co-facilitate this week’s Project Pericles Forum— “Towards Climate Resilience: How Do We Change Course on Climate Change?”

title: Project Pericles Forum: The Ukraine Affair  (October 3, 2019)
description: This week's Forum focuses on the quick-moving events surrounding the Ukraine Affair and Democrats' impeachment inquiry into President Trump's actions. Dr. Jay Barth will facilitate the Forum: "Impeachment: Moral Imperative or Rush to Judgment?"

title: First Tuesday Talk: Dr. Leslie Zorwick on supporting inclusive communities (Oct 1, 2019)
description: Dr. Zorwick will discuss how she thinks about supporting social justice as someone with social privilege. She will address how to be an effective ally to others so that our community works for everyone

title: Project Pericles Forum: Women in Politics (September 26, 2019)
description: Inspired by the upcoming Hendrix theatre production on suffrage, the Project Pericles Forum focuses on the current and future role of women in American politics. Join us for “100 Years After Suffrage: What Barriers Remain for Women in Politics?”

title: Project Pericles Forum: Protecting the Buffalo River (March 28, 2019)
description: This week's Project Pericles Forum focuses on the debate over how best to protect the Buffalo River. Dr. William Chaden Chomphosy and Maggie Young '19 will facilitate “Another Battle Over the Buffalo River: How Best to Protect It?”
